%% IPC Sequence: lifecycle of a reading and a rename in the Electron app.
sequenceDiagram
    participant Sensor as H5075 sensor
    participant CB as CoreBluetooth
    participant Main as main.js (Node)
    participant Pre as preload (IPC)
    participant UI as renderer/app.js

    Note over Main: app.whenReady() → setupNoble() + createWindow()
    Main->>CB: noble.startScanningAsync([], true)

    loop every ~2s per sensor
        Sensor-->>CB: BLE advertisement (0xEC88 payload)
        CB-->>Main: noble 'discover'(peripheral)
        Main->>Main: filter GVH507* + decodeH5075()
        Main->>Main: buildReading(name, names[name], decoded, rssi)
        Main-->>Pre: send('reading', reading)
        Pre-->>UI: onReading(reading)
        UI->>UI: update card, sparkline, alerts
        alt logging enabled & interval elapsed
            Main->>Main: store.appendReading(logs/…json)
        end
    end

    Note over UI: user edits a card name
    UI->>Pre: setName(device, "garage")
    Pre->>Main: invoke 'names:set'
    Main->>Main: store.saveNames(names.json)
    Main-->>UI: updated names map
    UI->>UI: toast "Renamed"
